---
// Four-step mechanism explainer. The widgets below are concrete views
// of each step; this is the map for the rest of the page.

const steps = [
  {
    n: 1,
    title: 'Trace',
    body: 'PEP 669 sys.monitoring records every function call. PEP 578 audit hooks classify each file open, network connection, subprocess spawn, and exec/eval as impure I/O so the cache never returns a value computed from something it didn’t see.',
  },
  {
    n: 2,
    title: 'Judge',
    body: 'A call is memoized only if four things hold: it ran long enough to be worth caching, it performed no impure I/O, it didn’t mutate its arguments, and its source plus transitive dependencies hash to a known key. Any single miss disqualifies the cache write.',
  },
  {
    n: 3,
    title: 'Store',
    body: 'The return value is serialized by type — Arrow IPC for DataFrames, numpy.save for arrays, safetensors for tensors, msgpack for primitives, cloudpickle as a fallback — and committed to a content-addressed SQLite cache. File dependencies are content-hashed so a `touch -r` can’t fool the cache.',
  },
  {
    n: 4,
    title: 'Replay',
    body: 'Next run: same call, same args, same file inputs return the cached value in microseconds. Any change to the source, the arguments, or a tracked file invalidates the entry and the function re-runs. The first run pays for the cache; every subsequent run benefits.',
  },
];
---

<section id="how" class="container-wide mt-24 scroll-mt-24" aria-labelledby="how-h">
  <header class="mb-8 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="eyebrow">02 — How it works</p>
    <h2 id="how-h" class="h-section mt-3">
      Four steps, in order
    </h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      The widgets below show what each step looks like in practice — the edit-rerun
      timeline visualises the replay step, the purity-gates panel decomposes the judge
      step, the serializer comparison covers store, and the live editor demonstrates the
      hash that makes step 4 possible.
    </p>
  </header>

  <ol class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-4">
    {steps.map((s) => (
      <li class="card p-5">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
          <span class="num text-2xl text-[var(--color-rote)]">{String(s.n).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
          <span class="eyebrow">{s.title}</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          <Fragment set:html={s.body.replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code>$1</code>')} />
        </p>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ol>

  <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
    Functions doing real I/O are skipped, not silently miscached:
    <code>rote.stats()["invalidation_reasons"]</code> records why each call missed
    (<code>calls impure stdlib: time.time</code>, <code>argument mutated</code>, and so
    on). Missed memoization is fine; stale results are not. Correctness is the contract;
    the speedups are the dividend.
  </p>
</section>
